# Vault/.env.example
#
# Template for Vault/.env — the real values file.
# Copy this to Vault/.env and fill in. Never commit .env.
#
# Every key listed here must also appear in Vault/key-inventory.md
# with a description of what it's for and which workflows/projects use it.

# === Anthropic / Claude ===
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# === GitHub ===
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# === Optional — not currently used ===
# These keys are kept here so a future gbrain install is one edit away.
# Current retrieval layer is the Google Drive MCP (see MASTER PLAN Phase 6).
# Re-enable these only if the vault grows past ~2,000 files and keyword
# search starts failing. See Vault/key-inventory.md for status.

# OpenAI — would be used by gbrain for embeddings
# Get from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Cost estimate: ~$0.10 for a small vault, ~$4-5 for 5,000+ pages.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Supabase — would be used by gbrain as the retrieval layer
# Postgres connection string from Supabase "Connect" → "Session pooler" tab.
# Format: postgresql://postgres.xxxxx:PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
# Port MUST be 6543 (Session pooler), not 5432.
# SUPABASE_POOLER_URL=

# === Processing / connectors (future) ===
# Add keys for each connector as you wire them up.
# HEPTABASE_API_KEY=
# GRANOLA_API_KEY=
# GMAIL_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN=
